1
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,120
There's one more thing.

2
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,440
I wanted to ask you.

3
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:37,520
On your way back just now,

4
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,360
did Zhang Du say anything?

5
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:41,880
He didn't say much.

6
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,800
Don't you know what your dad means?

7
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:53,840
Dad, are you still undecided

8
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,480
about whether to keep him or not?

9
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,720
What do you think?

10
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,600
I'd rather not give my opinion.

11
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:07,840
I'm heading out.

12
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:10,280
Son.

13
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:12,880
Xuan Yan.

14
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,400
Xuan Yan.

15
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:20,360
I know I usually

16
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,240
don't handle things well.

17
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:25,400
I always take it out on you.

18
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,320
This time, it's all up to you.

19
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:40,640
As long as you kids are okay,

20
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,080
that's better than anything.

21
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,560
I'm off.

22
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:48,000
Son.

23
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:49,080
Son.

24
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,640
When you're done, come home.

25
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:53,160
Don't forget your mom and dad are here.

26
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,480
I know.

27
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,280
Senior brother

28
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:23,920
Just leave the clothes there

29
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:24,760
I'll wash them

30
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,280
It's just two pieces

31
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,160
I can handle it myself

32
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:28,840
Two pieces, let me do it

33
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:30,040
You go rest

34
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:35,360
Zhang Du

35
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:35,800
Master's wife

36
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,240
Is something wrong?

37
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,360
I...

38
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,800
I came to say goodbye

39
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,640
Do you really have to leave?

40
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,480
Aren't you going to say goodbye to your master?

41
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,040
Alright, Master's wife

42
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,360
Master.

43
00:04:32,640 --> 00:04:34,800
I have been reckless and unworthy.

44
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,240
I'm sorry.

45
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:42,320
Let bygones be bygones.

46
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:44,760
What are your plans now?

47
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:46,200
Still making paper?

48
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,120
Yes.

49
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,760
Making Ancient-Method Paper.

50
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:53,960
Yes.

51
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:00,800
Master, whether you understand or not,

52
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,560
this is the only way for me.

53
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:06,320
Everyone walks their own path.

54
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,160
No one can walk it for another.

55
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:16,040
Zhang Du.

56
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,320
Master's wife.

57
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,200
I can't bear to see you go.

58
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,680
When the factory was struggling,

59
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:24,040
you never took a single cent.

60
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,320
Such devotion is rare.

61
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,720
Your master and I will never forget it.

62
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:32,680
But the Xuan family has its rules.

63
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,840
We can't owe you your wages.

64
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,720
And I don't have your account number.

65
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:41,120
Here are your wages and allowances

66
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:42,960
plus interest, bonuses, and such.

67
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,760
I've been saving it all for you.

68
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,400
I didn't take good care of you.

69
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:47,880
Take it.

70
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:49,240
No, Master's wife.

71
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:50,040
I can't accept this.

72
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:50,560
Take it.

73
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,680
You'll need money out there.

74
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,160
Take it.

75
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:54,240
Be good now, be good.

76
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:57,080
If you have nowhere to go,

77
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,760
this old house of mine,

78
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,560
though it's a bit old and shabby,

79
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,560
still,

80
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:06,800
you can come stay anytime.

81
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:09,240
When you've made something of yourself,

82
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,880
if you want to move out,

83
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,800
that's up to you.

84
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,360
Thank you, Master.

85
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,000
Thank you, Master's wife.

86
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:58,320
Our Twelve Beauties of Jinling series.

87
00:06:58,360 --> 00:07:00,480
These are the first six we're releasing.

88
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,120
Take a look.

89
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,120
The first six in this release,

90
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:04,120
we're offering at a special price today.

91
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,200
The other six will be released soon.

92
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,440
Each one better than the last.

93
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:08,920
Today,

94
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,000
it's our promotion day.

95
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,240
We're launching a 7th premium Hengheng.

96
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,360
If today you

97
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,240
collect all six of the previous ones,

98
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,640
today's premium Hengheng is yours free.

99
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,680
And right now,

100
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,120
the results are pretty good.

101
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:25,080
Our cultural booths draw a big crowd.

102
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,760
I'm getting more and more confident.

103
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,520
I'm

104
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,760
planning

105
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,520
to expand our Blind Box series

106
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:33,760
with a few more lines.

107
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,520
Like legendary Chinese figures,

108
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,360
Spirits of the Four Treasures of the Study

109
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:40,240
Whichever sells best,

110
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,560
we'll push as our flagship.

111
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,640
You just focus on your designs.

112
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:44,840
We'll back you all the way.

113
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,200
Here, this way.

114
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,000
But I wouldn't recommend

115
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,160
putting energy into horizontal expansion.

116
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:55,200
I think you should dig deeper vertically,

117
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,720
create characters with more cultural depth

118
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,520
and stories behind them.

119
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,920
If I'm understanding you right,

120
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,760
you're implying my work lacks depth.

121
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:06,680
I...

122
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,920
That's not what I meant.

123
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:09,120
I'm just saying,

124
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,560
while you're providing

125
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,520
Emotional Value to consumers,

126
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:14,000
your cultural foundation

127
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,320
could be a bit more substantial,

128
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:16,360
a bit richer.

129
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,320
It's just a suggestion.

130
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:22,760
President Xin, here's your coffee.

131
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,320
Hey, what are you laughing at?

132
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,640
It's kind of scary, so sudden.

133
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,800
No, I'm laughing because

134
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:29,760
you actually consider others' feelings now.

135
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,880
That's not really like you.

136
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,799
I was afraid if I was too blunt,

137
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:34,679
you couldn't handle it.

138
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:36,240
You haven't even tried.

139
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,679
How do you know I can't handle it?

140
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:38,240
Come on.

141
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,679
Say it straight. Let me hear.

142
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,720
My opinion is:

143
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:47,040
content first, narrative-driven.

144
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,880
Cultural products without cultural roots

145
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,520
are just fast-moving consumer goods.

146
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:54,280
And Emotional Value isn't to please buyers.

147
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:57,880
It's about creating emotional resonance.

148
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,360
And cultural products

149
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,000
must be built upon

150
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,800
the cultural foundation of Xuan paper.

151
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:06,800
Dig into the cultural logic of Xuan paper

152
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,000
and its handcrafted value,

153
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,120
and with your audience,

154
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,440
build a deep emotional connection.

155
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,360
Otherwise, it's like a dog chasing its tail,

156
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,520
just spinning in the fast-consumer cycle.

157
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:20,080
Well, that really stings.

158
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,240
Nicely done.

159
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,320
Hello

160
00:09:35,120 --> 00:09:36,360
I'll notify President Xin right away

161
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,760
Sister Xin

162
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:44,720
What is it?

163
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:47,000
The Chairman is at the company

164
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:49,360
He's calling all executives for 1-on-1s

165
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,240
You're the last one on the list

166
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:53,080
And I also heard

167
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,760
that apart from Vice President Zhang

168
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,760
no one knew the Chairman was coming today

169
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:58,560
When Vice President Zhang went to pick him up

170
00:09:58,560 --> 00:09:59,880
he didn't even bring a driver

171
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:00,880
Before the Chairman even arrived, he...

172
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:01,640
Get to the point

173
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:03,960
What the Chairman's asking about

174
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,000
is all about your cultural-creative work

175
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,720
What's there to ask about that?

176
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:11,360
The tree seeks calm but the wind blows on

177
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,680
You'd better handle this carefully

178
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:15,640
Whatever you do, don't clash with him

179
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,080
You know me

180
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:24,120
My biggest trait is being open-minded

181
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:28,000
I'm willing to trust everyone around me

182
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,120
But

183
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,120
that person has to be worthy of my trust

184
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:33,320
Understood

185
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:42,160
Sister Xin, look

186
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,760
Zhang. Accounts.

187
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,160
Whose number is this?

188
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,520
No idea

189
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,880
Probably someone's burner number

190
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,600
The meaning is pretty clear

191
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:00,640
Zhang

192
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,400
Vice President Zhang

193
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,240
Accounts

194
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,760
The Chairman is auditing the books

195
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:07,520
For an audit, he'd just call finance in

196
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,600
and that would be enough

197
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,880
He's not auditing the company's books

198
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,640
He's auditing mine

199
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,640
For the Chairman to act like this

200
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:19,240
is really disheartening

201
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:20,480
He trusts no one

202
00:11:20,480 --> 00:11:22,000
Who's going to work hard for him?

203
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,920
He trusts Vice President Zhang too much.

204
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:30,320
About that purchase on the 2nd,

205
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:31,240
Here's what happened

206
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,120
I asked Vice President Zhang to sign it

207
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,360
but he was away on a business trip

208
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,160
So I went to President Xin

209
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,600
She said production couldn't be delayed

210
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:43,360
So she told me to take the detailed list

211
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:44,240
and organize it clearly

212
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:47,480
and ensure the inventory logs were signed

213
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,520
and keep clear records

214
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,520
She even explained things to finance

215
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:52,720
saying to disburse the purchase funds first

216
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:56,000
and get Vice President Zhang to sign later

217
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,520
Afterwards, this was truly my fault

218
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,000
Once things got busy

219
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:04,880
I missed Vice President Zhang's signature

220
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:07,840
But

221
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:10,360
I guarantee the entire purchasing process

222
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,360
was fully documented

223
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,080
The amount matches previous ones exactly

224
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,640
All of this

225
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,480
you can verify yourself

226
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:29,840
Last month's entertainment expenses doubled

227
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,440
Are you aware of this?

228
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,920
I think this wooden one, you know,

229
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:53,280
sometimes I'm afraid

230
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,840
you have to consider the audience, right?

231
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,440
Chairman, thank you for the long trip.

232
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:00,680
Go on with your work.

233
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,200
You must be tired from the trip.

234
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:04,520
Here, here.

235
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:05,960
I made you a cup of coffee.

236
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:08,760
Thank you, thank you.

237
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:09,480
You're welcome.

238
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:17,280
You see,

239
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,080
it's the same coffee,

240
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:21,880
but yours tastes completely different.

241
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,120
Thank you for the compliment, Chairman.

242
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,040
I was on a business trip nearby,

243
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:25,760
so I dropped by to see you all.

244
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:26,440
Sit.

245
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,160
All of us

246
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:29,120
hope the Chairman

247
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,760
can visit us more often,

248
00:13:30,760 --> 00:13:32,400
give us some feedback,

249
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:35,000
so we'll have more room to improve.

250
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:37,760
Don't just think about advancing.

251
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,720
Sometimes retreating in big strides

252
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:43,000
is for advancing in big strides tomorrow.

253
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,600
I'd love to charge in tonight

254
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,360
and by tomorrow morning

255
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,640
wipe out the enemy's million-strong army.

256
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:50,000
But we can't, comrade.

257
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,920
Business is a battlefield.

258
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,120
President Xin,

259
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,120
I

260
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:58,360
want to discuss something with you.

261
00:13:58,680 --> 00:13:59,480
Go ahead.

262
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:02,760
Let's end the Blind Box project here.

263
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,400
Starting today,

264
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,760
all of the company's business

265
00:14:05,760 --> 00:14:07,240
returns to thread-bound books.

266
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:13,480
Chairman, perhaps you're not fully aware

267
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:15,120
of the current status of this project.

268
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,240
I don't need to be aware.

269
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,720
This is the group's decision.

270
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,160
Then,

271
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,880
may I know why?

272
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:29,400
Does a group decision need a reason?

273
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:33,760
Chairman,

274
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:36,880
when this project first started,

275
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:39,120
I promised everyone the world.

276
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,840
If we suddenly halt it now,

277
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:43,160
I need to give everyone an explanation.

278
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:44,480
Otherwise,

279
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,280
I won't be able to do my job going forward.

280
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,360
No one will believe anything I say.

281
00:14:58,640 --> 00:14:59,480
President Xin,

282
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:01,800
you're pressuring me here.

283
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:02,880
I'm not pressuring you.

284
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,600
I just want your trust.

285
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:08,840
I've been giving this project my all.

286
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,800
I'm doing this for your own good.

287
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,440
Why don't you understand?

288
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,160
The company's returns must exceed 50%.

289
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,720
That was your own promise, wasn't it?

290
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,760
You haven't forgotten, have you?

291
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,000
I haven't forgotten.

292
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,480
I can do it.

293
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:24,640
How will you do it?

294
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,240
Chairman,

295
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,400
right now in the market

296
00:15:27,400 --> 00:15:29,480
we're getting very positive feedback.

297
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,840
We just need a little more time.

298
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,400
I believe...

299
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,600
It's not about you believing.

300
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,000
It's about me believing,

301
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,520
and the market believing.

302
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,520
What's the top principle of management?

303
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,160
Controllable risk, right?

304
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:41,120
It's not gambling.

305
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,800
Eight million just went down the drain.

306
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:44,600
And the returns?

307
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,120
I haven't seen any returns.

308
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,040
Chairman

309
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,360
Are you questioning the 8-million expense?

310
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,520
I give you eight million,

311
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:03,240
and you bring back ten million.

312
00:16:03,240 --> 00:16:04,880
Of course I'd happily put all the money

313
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,360
straight into your own pocket.

314
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:09,400
So the Chairman is now suspecting me?

315
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,000
I won't hear it.

316
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,880
I'll emphasize just one thing.

317
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,360
Starting today,

318
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,960
Dayazhai will not spend a single cent

319
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,000
on the Blind Box project.

320
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,120
Stop, all of you, stop!

321
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,600
Drop everything you're working on, now!

322
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:31,520
Old Huang, come here.

323
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:33,800
What is all this?

324
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,240
Working day and night

325
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,840
just to make this money-losing junk?

326
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:39,960
It's just a waste of time!

327
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:40,400
This, this...

328
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,720
Look at what this is!

329
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,840
Isn't the company's loss still a loss?

330
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,400
Let me tell you,

331
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:46,680
from this point on,

332
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,120
any work related to these lousy Blind Boxes,

333
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,040
stop it all, right now!

334
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:51,400
As for the next step,

335
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:53,240
wait for me to assign it in a meeting.

336
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,480
Oh, right.

337
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:55,160
Hurry up

338
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:56,720
and bring this quarter's financial reports

339
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:58,000
to my office.

340
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:58,880
Immediately.

341
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:07,880
Boss, has there been a change?

342
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:31,640
Stop looking at me.

343
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,760
Xuan Yan, let me toast you again.

344
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,240
Let this meal

345
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,600
be our farewell dinner.

346
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:41,360
Wait, hold on, hold on, hold on.

347
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,440
Don't talk about breaking up yet.

348
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,520
You just said your Vice President Zhang,

349
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:46,520
representing the Chairman,

350
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,880
shut down the cultural production line.

351
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,280
So the 50% growth

352
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,400
you promised your Chairman

353
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,840
just goes up in smoke?

354
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,880
Next, Vice President Zhang

355
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,520
will fully take over your company.

356
00:17:56,520 --> 00:17:58,760
You'll have no place left in the company.

357
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:00,520
Everything you said is right.

358
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:02,520
But right now I have no options.

359
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:03,960
There's nothing I can do.

360
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:06,040
Sister Xin seems tough on the outside,

361
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,600
but she's still too kind-hearted.

362
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,000
Otherwise, how would a petty upstart

363
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,360
like Vice President Zhang get his way?

364
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:11,520
And the Chairman,

365
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:13,880
did Vice President Zhang brainwash him?

366
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,760
Yuqing, the Chairman faces huge pressure.

367
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:18,280
The group is preparing for its IPO.

368
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:19,960
There's no room for any mistakes.

369
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,360
And you're still defending him?

370
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:22,600
Xin Ran,

371
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:24,960
it's not that there's nothing you can do.

372
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:26,880
During our time working together,

373
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:29,760
you've been doing everything.

374
00:18:30,280 --> 00:18:31,760
Now leave the rest to me.

375
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,760
Not only will we keep the business going,

376
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,440
we'll learn how to fight back.

377
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:39,240
We have to handle things one at a time.

378
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,680
The most important thing right now

379
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:43,320
is finding third-party funding for backup.

380
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,320
As long as we have third-party capital

381
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,280
investing in the project,

382
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:47,920
we're bound to win this fight.

383
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,440
The promises you made your Chairman

384
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,480
can all be fulfilled.

385
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,840
Do you know what you should do right now?

386
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,400
Go tell your Chairman

387
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:56,040
that stopping now

388
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:58,760
means early investments go down the drain.

389
00:18:58,760 --> 00:18:59,720
And now

390
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,480
that the funding is in place,

391
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:02,520
even if we lose,

392
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:03,800
he won't suffer any loss.

393
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,600
I know you want to help me.

394
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:07,040
But Xuan Yan, do you realize

395
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,760
we'll need two to three million more?

396
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,040
Where will you find that kind of money?

397
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,480
Don't you worry about that.

398
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,080
I have my own piggy bank.

399
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,000
Piggy bank?

400
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:27,000
Out with it.

401
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:28,760
What kind of trap

402
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:31,720
are you setting for me this time?

403
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,720
Tricking you into getting rich.

404
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,200
You say that every time.

405
00:19:37,280 --> 00:19:38,560
I'm sick and tired of it.

406
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:39,400
Try something new.

407
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:41,440
I was thinking

408
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,720
of cutting you in on some money.

409
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,280
Guess I'll just

410
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:46,800
work with President Xin on my own.

411
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,560
Just give me the gist.

412
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,440
Forget it.

413
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,320
It's all just my scheming.

414
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:55,440
You lay your traps,

415
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:57,200
whether I fall in is up to me.

416
00:19:58,520 --> 00:19:59,800
Aren't you being tacky?

417
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,000
Toying with me, huh?

418
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,080
Fine. Xuan Yan.

419
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:03,080
Comrade Xiao Min,

420
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:05,200
I take this conversation very seriously.

421
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:06,960
Please sit down and hear me out.

422
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:13,160
Go ahead.

423
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:17,280
Actually, there's no need for you to rush.

424
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,160
In your current state,

425
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:22,640
even if things develop with President Xin,

426
00:20:23,080 --> 00:20:24,920
it'll only ever be friendship.

427
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,800
Awkwardly calling each other bro and sis,

428
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:30,080
it will never be the sweet romance

429
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:31,240
you've been longing for.

430
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:32,440
You know why?

431
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,240
Why?

432
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:36,800
President Xin isn't into your type at all.

433
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:40,680
You two are on completely different levels.

434
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:42,720
You're on the basic level,

435
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,520
content with food on the table,

436
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:46,200
and you're satisfied.

437
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,520
But President Xin? What's she?

438
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:48,920
She's on the top tier.

439
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:50,920
What she pursues

440
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:53,680
is maximizing her own self-worth.

441
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,320
No, no, no.

442
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:55,840
You're making my head spin.

443
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:57,280
Can you just say it plainly?

444
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:58,080
What do you mean?

445
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,840
Upgrade your own tier.

446
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,320
Get into the culture industry.

447
00:21:03,120 --> 00:21:05,920
Isn't making paper the culture industry?

448
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,880
What does your business license say?

449
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:10,040
Production and processing, manufacturing.

450
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,560
Does it say "culture" anywhere?

451
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,240
Then how do I go about it?

452
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:16,240
How? Doing what?

453
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:18,040
Something that raises your tier,

454
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,560
and also lets you and President Xin

455
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:21,160
take your relationship

456
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,960
to the next level.

457
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,320
Partner with President Xin in culture.

458
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:29,360
Two birds, one stone.

459
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:30,920
President Xin, right now,

460
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:32,640
is going through a rough patch.

461
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,600
If you lend her a hand right now,

462
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:35,960
and give her your full support,

463
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,000
what do you call that?

464
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,320
That's a hero saving the damsel.

465
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:40,800
That's double the impact.

466
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:43,160
That's Emotional Value maxed out.

467
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,880
I get it, I get it.

468
00:21:44,880 --> 00:21:45,960
This idea of yours is really great.

469
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,240
It's a good thing, a good thing.

470
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:49,240
But this culture industry,

471
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,480
I really don't know a thing about it.

472
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:51,000
So tell me,

473
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:52,720
are the market prospects any good?

474
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,480
You tell me.

475
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,040
It doesn't matter if you understand it.

476
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:56,160
You've got me, don't you?

477
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,760
Now, tell me right now...

478
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,520
Come in.

479
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:04,640
President Xin.

480
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:07,520
Hello, President Xin.

481
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:09,240
Hello, President Xin. Hello.

482
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,000
I've come to learn from you.

483
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,920
And find some room to grow.

484
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:14,520
Learn from you, learn from you.

485
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:15,720
President Xiao, you're too kind.

486
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:16,560
Please, have a seat.

487
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:17,040
Sure.

488
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,000
I'll pour you some tea.

489
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:18,480
No, no, no.

490
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:19,760
I'm not thirsty. Not thirsty at all.

491
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,160
President Xiao, are you hot?

492
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,200
I'll turn the AC down a bit.

493
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,720
No, no, no. Don't trouble yourself.

494
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,080
I'll just unbutton this.

495
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Honestly speaking,

496
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
I usually dress pretty casually.

497
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:34,080
But today, just to meet you,

498
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,600
that's why I dressed so formally.

499
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:38,520
Since we're going to be family from now on,

500
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:40,840
I don't need to be so formal, right?

501
00:22:45,280 --> 00:22:46,080
President Xiao,

502
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,240
the production plan I sent over,

503
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,760
along with the financial statements,

504
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:51,160
have you looked through them?

505
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:53,000
You really didn't need to send them.

506
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:55,800
I have absolute trust in you, President Xin.

507
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:58,240
Trust is just the basis of cooperation.

508
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,280
Once we have that trust,

509
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,320
our future development

510
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,840
will go much more smoothly.

511
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,320
So I still

512
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:05,480
hope you'll look closely, President Xiao.

513
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:08,000
After all, this is no small investment.

514
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:11,080
It's all well within my means.

515
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:13,600
You can rest assured about my capability.

516
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:15,000
As for the second round of funding,

517
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:18,000
I've decided that once the project reaches

518
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,840
the promotional campaign phase,

519
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:20,960
I'll follow up promptly.

520
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:24,400
That'll help avoid any capacity issues.

521
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:26,800
What are you laughing at?

522
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:29,520
President Xiao, oh, President Xiao.

523
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:33,840
You've read the proposal very carefully.

524
00:23:38,560 --> 00:23:39,520
This proposal,

525
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,920
you worked so hard on it, President Xin.

526
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:43,440
If I didn't read it carefully,

527
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:44,840
I'd really be letting you down.

528
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:45,640
Don't worry.

529
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:47,840
I'll do everything in my power

530
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:49,560
to secure your returns, President Xiao.

531
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,240
Good.

532
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:52,760
Wonderful.

533
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:00,280
So beautiful!

534
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,240
President Xiao.

535
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:07,520
Shall I have someone show you the workshop?

536
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:08,280
No, no, no.

537
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:09,760
Your management skills,

538
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:11,280
I've long since witnessed them.

539
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,960
I have complete confidence.

540
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,400
On production and sales,

541
00:24:14,400 --> 00:24:15,560
I won't interfere at all.

542
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,240
I'll only be in charge of solving

543
00:24:18,800 --> 00:24:19,680
the money problems.

544
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:25,160
I'm truly so grateful

545
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,160
for your timely help, President Xiao.

546
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,680
No need to thank me, no need at all.

547
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:31,800
You have so many books here.

548
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:34,040
So many books.

549
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:38,760
So many books.

550
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:42,240
Have you read them all?

551
00:24:42,520 --> 00:24:43,320
President Xiao.

552
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,520
Was there something else?

553
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:48,760
What... what do you mean?

554
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:50,400
Auntie Xin!

555
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,200
Why did you come in again?

556
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,320
Didn't I tell you to wait outside?

557
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,040
You...

558
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:56,600
This kid never listens.

559
00:24:56,600 --> 00:24:58,200
Auntie Xin, I just took a look around.

560
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,280
Your place is amazing.

561
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:00,800
Compared to this, my dad's factory

562
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:01,960
looks totally shabby.

563
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:02,960
This kid...

564
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:04,680
Just got off school,

565
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:05,960
and kept pestering me,

566
00:25:05,960 --> 00:25:07,040
insisting on coming to see you.

567
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,240
Said she missed you.

568
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,440
I just love Auntie Xin.

569
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,400
Auntie loves you too.

570
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:14,480
I even dreamed about you at school.

571
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,720
What did you dream about Auntie?

572
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,160
Dad.

573
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:18,960
Are you

574
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:21,600
trying to have me play matchmaker for you?

575
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:22,720
Smart girl.

576
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:25,040
Truly my daughter.

577
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,280
You're so old,

578
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,840
your face is all wrinkled when you smile,

579
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:33,240
and yet your skin is so thin.

580
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,840
How could Auntie Xin Ran ever like you?

581
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:41,760
That's why Dad's asking for your help.

582
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,160
I can help you,

583
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:46,320
but I have my principles.

584
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,240
Go on.

585
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:50,800
How much money are you asking for?

586
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:51,720
A thousand.

587
00:26:03,160 --> 00:26:04,800
Oh, you're too kind-hearted.

588
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:06,800
That Vice President Zhang of yours,

589
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,320
he's just waiting for his moment,

590
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:09,600
lying in wait on your path,

591
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:10,840
ready the instant he sees an opening

592
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,240
to sink his fangs into you like a viper.

593
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,200
Right.

594
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:14,480
We need to hit him hard,

595
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:16,240
pull out all his venomous fangs.

596
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,520
Otherwise, endless trouble awaits.

597
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,200
I know what to do.

598
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,040
Our Dayazhai

599
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:37,840
has a contract with Wu Yuliang in town.

600
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:40,800
All paper scraps from our production line

601
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:41,840
all go to him.

602
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:42,600
Per year,

603
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:45,160
he pays us 100,000 yuan.

604
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:46,480
But

605
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:49,760
I know Vice President Zhang often sneaks

606
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:52,760
the paper scraps to scrap yards to sell.

607
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,960
And he's made quite a bit.

608
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,440
Mr. Zhang, Mr. Zhang is here.

609
00:27:00,080 --> 00:27:01,720
Mr. Zhang, you're here.

610
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:02,320
Don't, don't, don't.

611
00:27:02,320 --> 00:27:04,000
Cut the act.

612
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:05,400
What do you mean?

613
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:07,480
Two tons? Impossible.

614
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:09,720
I weighed it properly at the factory.

615
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:10,760
Three and a half tons.

616
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:11,920
It's definitely two tons.

617
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:13,040
When it was weighed,

618
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,680
I took photos. Let me show you.

619
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:17,280
I don't need to see. I see these.

620
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,120
Who's this?

621
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,080
What are you doing?

622
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,520
Hurry up, get down here now.

623
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:28,760
Boss,

624
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:30,000
I'm renovating my house.

625
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:32,040
I want to buy some scrap cardboard.

626
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:34,240
I've packed them all. Not selling.

627
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,240
Boss,

628
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,680
I'll pay you a little extra.

629
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:37,440
Do me a favor.

630
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:38,360
I need them urgently.

631
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,520
Okay, then wait a moment.

632
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:41,240
Okay, okay.

633
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:42,720
Let me tell you, Old Seven,

634
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,840
don't try any tricks with me.

635
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:47,000
Otherwise, we won't work together anymore.

636
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,160
Mr. Zhang, calm down, calm down.

637
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:50,840
I'll count it as three tons then.

638
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:51,560
No more haggling.

639
00:27:51,560 --> 00:27:52,280
Fine.

640
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,280
All right.

641
00:27:53,760 --> 00:27:55,760
Just transfer the money to me quickly.

642
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:56,680
Okay.

643
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:02,160
Mr. Zhang, take it easy.

644
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,560
Drive safe, Mr. Zhang.

645
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:06,600
How many did you want just now?

646
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:07,840
Weren't you asking for cardboard?

647
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:08,960
About the cardboard,

648
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,520
I'll ask my wife tomorrow.

649
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:12,240
Weren't you in a hurry just now?

650
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:13,920
She's not in a hurry.

651
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:15,200
This matter is urgent.

652
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:15,800
What are you...

653
00:28:15,800 --> 00:28:17,240
What are you doing? Who are you?

654
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:19,440
Know Wu Yuliang from the scrap company?

655
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,040
Who doesn't know Mr. Wu?

656
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,560
He's the top boss in our industry.

657
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,440
I'm Mr. Wu's assistant.

658
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:26,200
Let's have a chat.

659
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,040
You asked for it.

660
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:37,240
Let's handle this as it should be handled.

661
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:50,680
You can't guard against a thief within.

662
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:53,240
I pay my lease fees on time every year,

663
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:54,720
and you steal from me and sell it off?

664
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,040
You want everyone to find out, huh?

665
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,520
I've got the video right here!

666
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:59,320
I'll call the cops right now to arrest you!

667
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:01,440
I'm sorry!

668
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:04,000
Can't we talk this out?

669
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,320
Talk, my ass!

670
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:07,240
Watch yourself when working for me!

671
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:09,600
Enough, stop hitting him!

672
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:10,800
Stop it!

673
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,480
Come on, get back to what you were doing.

674
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:13,720
Watching a show, huh?

675
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:14,760
Enough!

676
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,800
President Wu, stop!

677
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:18,800
President Wu!

678
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:20,800
If someone at Dayazhai messed up,

679
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:22,720
we can settle it properly.

680
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:23,920
Lose the fight, but keep your dignity.

681
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:25,840
You're beating and cursing him on my turf.

682
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:26,920
That's hardly appropriate.

683
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:28,040
I'm not making a scene.

684
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:30,760
I just ask President Xin for justice.

685
00:29:32,240 --> 00:29:33,560
Alright. Yuqing,

686
00:29:33,760 --> 00:29:35,000
please take President Wu and his men

687
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,240
to the reception room for some tea.

688
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:37,280
This way, please.

689
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:38,680
Right this way.

690
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:40,840
If you don't give me an answer today,

691
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,240
I won't let him off.

692
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:44,960
Alright,

693
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:45,920
get up.

694
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:47,000
Stop embarrassing yourself.

695
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:47,960
Let's talk inside.

696
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:50,680
Xin, Xin, Xin...

697
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,680
Please, help me!

698
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,920
I was such a jerk before.

699
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,400
In front of the Chairman,

700
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,760
I even ratted on you.

701
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:01,320
I went against you at every turn.

702
00:30:01,720 --> 00:30:05,240
I swear I'll never do it again, okay?

703
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:05,680
You...

704
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,000
Let go.

705
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,520
Please help me, help me!

706
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:10,680
I'll be at your beck and call from now on.

707
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,200
Please save me, save me!

708
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:13,240
Don't talk about it out here.

709
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,000
Let's go inside.

710
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:31,520
You're in serious trouble now.

711
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:35,560
If the Chairman finds out about this,

712
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:39,000
you won't be able to stay at Dayazhai.

713
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:43,080
Getting fired isn't even the main problem.

714
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:46,240
Wu Yuliang has you cornered now.

715
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:49,080
If he really presses charges,

716
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:50,000
Yuqing.

717
00:30:50,240 --> 00:30:51,040
Did you look it up?

718
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:52,520
Yes, I did.

719
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:53,560
According to the Criminal Law,

720
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:55,320
Article 264,

721
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:57,080
theft of public or private property

722
00:30:57,560 --> 00:31:00,080
involving 30,000 to under 100,000 yuan

723
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,280
carries a sentence of three to ten years,

724
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:03,400
plus a fine.

725
00:31:04,240 --> 00:31:05,600
The scrapyard owner confessed

726
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:07,760
Vice President Zhang sold to him 3 times.

727
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:10,240
What's the total amount?

728
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:11,760
I'd rather not say.

729
00:31:15,440 --> 00:31:16,240
President Xin,

730
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:17,600
I can't go to prison.

731
00:31:17,600 --> 00:31:19,560
I've got elderly parents and young kids.

732
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:22,200
I'm begging you, please help me.

733
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:25,040
I'll wait on you hand and foot from now on.

734
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:26,680
I'll burn the first incense for you.

735
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:27,600
I'm not dead yet.

736
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:30,840
Stop crying.

737
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:33,480
Yuqing.

738
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:34,680
Go invite President Wu in.

739
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:35,320
Okay.

740
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:50,440
President Wu,

741
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,000
please have a seat.

742
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:54,360
So how do we handle this?

743
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:56,320
Do you pay compensation,

744
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:57,440
or do I call the police?

745
00:31:57,520 --> 00:31:58,480
Sit down and let's talk.

746
00:31:58,480 --> 00:31:59,240
Have some tea first.

747
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,200
President Wu,

748
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:03,760
about this matter,

749
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:05,280
I've got a clear picture now.

750
00:32:05,520 --> 00:32:06,520
Strictly speaking,

751
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:09,800
it's between you and Vice President Zhang.

752
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,760
It has nothing to do with Dayazhai.

753
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:12,760
I could get involved,

754
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:13,800
or I could stay out of it.

755
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:16,240
But,

756
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,960
considering all the years you've

757
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:19,960
worked with our company,

758
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:22,440
I can put myself in your shoes

759
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:24,160
and offer you two pieces of advice.

760
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,520
Not sure if you'll hear me out.

761
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:26,240
Go ahead.

762
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,520
You can press charges

763
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:28,560
and send him to prison.

764
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:31,840
But there's one thing

765
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:33,600
I need to remind you of.

766
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:35,680
Vice President Zhang

767
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:38,240
is someone our Chairman deeply trusts.

768
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:39,520
If you push this too far

769
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:41,080
and get him locked up,

770
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:43,240
then your business with Dayazhai

771
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:44,600
comes to an end.

772
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:46,440
I can drop the charges,

773
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,520
but he still has to pay up, right?

774
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,800
That's exactly my second point.

775
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:53,040
President Wu,

776
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:55,760
you and I don't know each other.

777
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:57,840
I've never had a bite of food from you,

778
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,720
never had a sip of tea from you either.

779
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:02,920
So there's no personal history between us.

780
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:03,920
As for you,

781
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:07,080
you signed with our former GM.

782
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:09,760
Dayazhai gives you a year's paper scraps

783
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:11,440
at a package price of 100,000.

784
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,480
You've made a killing already, haven't you?

785
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:19,920
But now I'm Dayazhai's general manager.

786
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:21,520
President Wu.

787
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,720
Let me be honest with you.

788
00:33:24,760 --> 00:33:26,400
Our contract expires this year.

789
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:28,200
I don't want to renew it with you.

790
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,560
I did a rough calculation.

791
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:31,240
It's about 500,000 to 600,000 a year.

792
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:32,920
So why on earth

793
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,720
should I let you earn that money?

794
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:37,600
I can use my company's own connections.

795
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:39,200
President Xin.

796
00:33:39,320 --> 00:33:40,560
I've heard, you know,

797
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,560
that this guy doesn't treat you well.

798
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,560
Yet here you are helping him.

799
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:44,680
For your sake,

800
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:45,760
even if we don't cooperate,

801
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:46,760
I'll still sue him and put him away.

802
00:33:46,760 --> 00:33:47,520
President Wu.

803
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:49,240
Whether he treats me well

804
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:51,720
is an internal matter of our company.

805
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,240
It's none of your business.

806
00:33:53,320 --> 00:33:55,000
And if you really want to sue him,

807
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,440
you might not even succeed.

808
00:33:57,560 --> 00:34:00,080
Those papers he hauled to the scrapyard,

809
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,680
if I say they're paper scraps,

810
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:03,920
then they're paper scraps.

811
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:05,480
If I say they're finished paper,

812
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:06,720
then they're finished paper.

813
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:07,760
How they're classified

814
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:08,840
is up to me.

815
00:34:09,159 --> 00:34:10,000
So now,

816
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,760
I'm telling you,

817
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:14,760
those are our company's finished paper.

818
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:17,320
This matter has nothing to do with you.

819
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:21,800
If you put it that way,

820
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:23,760
I have nothing more to say.

821
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,239
But

822
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,239
you can't just let me swallow this loss.

823
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,520
President Wu, didn't I just say?

824
00:34:30,719 --> 00:34:32,840
I originally didn't want to work with you.

825
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:36,520
But since you're giving me face today,

826
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:38,600
I'll leave you a way to make money.

827
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:39,719
The contract,

828
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,199
we'll keep signing it.

829
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:45,080
Fine.

830
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,520
Since President Xin is being so generous,

831
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:49,760
I won't hold it against him.

832
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:51,560
Next time,

833
00:34:51,719 --> 00:34:52,760
I'll bring you some tea.

834
00:34:53,520 --> 00:34:54,960
Kid, you'd better learn from this.

835
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,199
Thank President Xin properly.

836
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,000
President Xin.

837
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:57,760
I'll be off now.

838
00:35:00,800 --> 00:35:02,000
Take care, President Wu.

839
00:35:04,720 --> 00:35:05,520
President Xin.

840
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:06,520
Thank you.

841
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:07,480
Your great kindness,

842
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,760
I'll never forget it.

843
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:12,000
What are you doing?

844
00:35:14,560 --> 00:35:16,040
From now on, you're my godmother.

845
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,200
Let go.

846
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,520
Never seen Vice President Zhang so tame.

847
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:24,960
Reporting in morning and night,

848
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:26,520
treating your every word as gospel.

849
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:29,920
But I think you're still too merciful.

850
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:31,400
Someone like Vice President Zhang

851
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,520
should be dealt with harshly.

852
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:33,520
Sentence him to a few years.

853
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:37,280
After all, he has a family to support.

854
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:39,480
Give people a break when you can.

855
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,560
If I get rid of Vice President Zhang,

856
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:43,320
the group will just send someone else,

857
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:44,680
President Li, President Tang.

858
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:46,520
I'd still have to keep fighting them.

859
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:50,440
If all my energy goes into scheming,

860
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:52,560
how can Dayazhai keep developing?

861
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:54,520
You've got a point.

862
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,560
Keeping the status quo is fine too.

863
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:10,440
Family of Su Min,

864
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,600
take the slip and pay the fee.

865
00:36:41,040 --> 00:36:41,880
Taozi.

866
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:43,520
You're up, right?

867
00:36:49,120 --> 00:36:50,200
Yeah, well...

868
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:52,600
I'm at the hospital picking up...

869
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:54,120
picking up my mom to check out.

870
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:54,920
So, um...

871
00:36:57,040 --> 00:36:58,400
Could you lend me some money?

872
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,160
I'll pay you back later.

873
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,120
Thanks, Taozi.

874
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:12,120
Yiran.

875
00:37:13,520 --> 00:37:15,000
Did you finish the discharge paperwork?

876
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:17,320
There's so much stuff you need to pack up.

877
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,280
These clothes are so uncomfortable.

878
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:20,640
I need to change right away.

879
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:31,000
Auntie.

880
00:37:32,280 --> 00:37:33,760
Mom and I are on our way.

881
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:36,240
Yeah, she just got discharged.

882
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:37,760
But she's recovering pretty well.

883
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:41,720
Okay, see you in a bit.

884
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:43,240
Thanks, Auntie.

885
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:47,000
What do you mean?

886
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:48,920
We're not going home?

887
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:50,120
Where are we going?

888
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:52,920
We'll stay at Auntie's for a couple days.

889
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:55,320
Look at your uncle-in-law, what a half-wit.

890
00:37:55,640 --> 00:37:56,840
I can't stand looking at his face.

891
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:57,560
I'm not going.

892
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:01,600
If you don't like him, just ignore him.

893
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:03,040
Besides, he plays cards every day.

894
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:04,320
He barely comes home anyway.

895
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:08,920
Mom, let me be honest with you.

896
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:10,120
I don't have much money right now.

897
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:11,600
I can't afford to hire a caregiver for you.

898
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:13,080
What I earn isn't even as much as...

899
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:15,920
I don't even earn as much as a caregiver.

900
00:38:15,920 --> 00:38:16,680
You know?

901
00:38:17,440 --> 00:38:19,320
Did I ask you to hire a caregiver?

902
00:38:19,840 --> 00:38:21,160
I already said I can manage.

903
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:23,040
I'm perfectly fine at home by myself.

904
00:38:23,040 --> 00:38:24,400
I can take care of myself.

905
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:25,560
Driver, pull over.

906
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:26,840
I'm not going.

907
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:27,520
Mom, what are you doing?

908
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:28,920
Pull over! I said pull over!

909
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:29,880
Mom, can't you put yourself in my shoes?

910
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,160
Think about me for once.

911
00:38:34,800 --> 00:38:35,920
Put myself in your shoes?

912
00:38:36,160 --> 00:38:37,520
It'd be best if you got transferred back.

913
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,440
Mom, are you being reasonable at all?

914
00:38:47,720 --> 00:38:48,520
Driver.

915
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:50,760
Turn around.

916
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:53,160
To Taohua Town.

917
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:53,960
Got it.

918
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:00,240
Yiran.

919
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:01,120
How's it going?

920
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:02,280
Did you bring Auntie back?

921
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:04,000
Just got here.

922
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:06,800
So where are you having her stay?

923
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:08,440
I don't know yet.

924
00:39:08,440 --> 00:39:09,840
I was thinking of getting Mom food first,

925
00:39:09,840 --> 00:39:11,480
then finding her a place to stay.

926
00:39:11,480 --> 00:39:12,600
Why go through all that trouble?

927
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:13,560
She can stay in our dorm.

928
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,760
I'll make room for Auntie.

929
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:16,320
No need, that's too much trouble.

930
00:39:17,720 --> 00:39:19,360
If Auntie stays here,

931
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,320
I can just go stay at my bestie's place.

932
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:22,600
Go get some food for Auntie.

933
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,760
I'll head to the dorm to check on her.

934
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,480
Thank you, Taozi.

935
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,040
You can watch it now.

936
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:39,840
But, Uncle,

937
00:39:39,960 --> 00:39:41,520
I have to warn you upfront.

938
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:43,080
Once you start binging these mini-dramas,

939
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:44,640
you just can't stop.

940
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:46,520
I don't have time to watch during the day.

941
00:39:46,520 --> 00:39:47,960
I'll just watch a bit at night.

942
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:50,440
This doesn't cost money, right?

943
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:52,800
Is there money on your phone?

944
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,000
Oh, right.

945
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:57,520
Your mom manages all my money.

946
00:39:59,640 --> 00:40:02,040
That time... how do I...

947
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:18,000
Dad.

948
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,960
That little album of Qianlong Jade Paper,

949
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:22,320
you made it for me, didn't you?

950
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:24,320
What nonsense are you on about?

951
00:40:25,080 --> 00:40:26,000
I said,

952
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:27,960
that little album of Qianlong Jade Paper,

953
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:29,280
you made it for me, right?

954
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:30,960
Can't hear you. I'm working.

955
00:40:31,320 --> 00:40:33,320
I know you're working, so I'm asking.

956
00:40:35,800 --> 00:40:37,160
What Qianlong Jade Paper?

957
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:39,400
Why are you meddling in everything?

958
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:41,320
Sounds pretty profitable.

959
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:42,280
Get back to work.

960
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:43,480
You can't leave me out of this.

961
00:40:45,560 --> 00:40:46,960
You little rascal.

962
00:40:48,640 --> 00:40:49,600
I'm just asking.

963
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:50,400
Up ahead there.

964
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:50,840
Director Hao.

965
00:40:51,880 --> 00:40:53,280
That's our Secretary Peng.

966
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:54,040
Secretary Peng.

967
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:56,800
This is Yiran's mother.

968
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:57,800
She's here to see you.

969
00:40:58,480 --> 00:40:59,600
Oh, Yiran's mother.

970
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:00,840
Hello, hello, hello.

971
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:02,760
Have you eaten yet?

972
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:03,280
Come on, come on.

973
00:41:03,280 --> 00:41:04,240
Grab a bite at the canteen.

974
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,400
No, no, no.

975
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:06,080
I won't eat.

976
00:41:06,200 --> 00:41:09,040
I just want a quick word alone with you.

977
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:10,120
Okay.

978
00:41:10,120 --> 00:41:11,040
Let's talk in the office.

979
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:12,480
No, no.

980
00:41:12,560 --> 00:41:13,960
No need to go to the office.

981
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,440
Just a couple of words.

982
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:16,560
I'll be quick.

983
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:17,440
Alright, alright.

984
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:19,520
What is it? Go ahead.

985
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:21,520
It's like this.

986
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:24,360
Our Yiran, she's still young.

987
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:26,280
She didn't really discuss it with me,

988
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,160
and just took the exam to come here.

989
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:29,600
No, no.

990
00:41:29,600 --> 00:41:31,920
I'm not saying Taohua Town isn't good.

991
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:32,720
That's not what I mean.

992
00:41:33,320 --> 00:41:34,120
The main thing is,

993
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,920
it's just too far from our home.

994
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:42,440
Her dad has passed away,

995
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,120
and my health hasn't been great lately.

996
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:46,640
I...

997
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,320
Yiran's mother,

998
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,720
just tell me directly what you want.

999
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:53,960
Secretary Peng, you have kids, right?

1000
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:54,680
Yes, I do.

1001
00:41:54,920 --> 00:41:55,720
See?

1002
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:57,440
That's great, then.

1003
00:41:57,480 --> 00:42:00,320
Who wants their kid in the countryside?

1004
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:01,600
And she's just a young girl.

1005
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,680
When she gets married and has kids someday,

1006
00:42:03,840 --> 00:42:05,560
it'll be so inconvenient.

1007
00:42:05,600 --> 00:42:08,320
Kids can't see that far ahead.

1008
00:42:08,480 --> 00:42:09,680
As mothers,

1009
00:42:09,720 --> 00:42:11,280
we have to plan for their future.

1010
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:12,000
Don't you agree?

1011
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:12,840
Yiran's mother,

1012
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:14,520
you've said so much,

1013
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:17,000
but what exactly do you want me to do?

1014
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:18,200
Secretary Peng,

1015
00:42:19,280 --> 00:42:20,680
you're Ranran's boss.

1016
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:21,880
Please, do us a favor.

1017
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:23,720
Transfer her to the county.

1018
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,640
Even a temporary assignment would do.

1019
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:28,480
As long as you can make this happen,

1020
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:30,920
we'll be forever grateful to you.

1021
00:42:31,200 --> 00:42:32,160
Yiran's mother,

1022
00:42:33,160 --> 00:42:33,960
actually,

1023
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:38,040
many cadres in our town are young people,

1024
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:40,200
and many aren't from around here.

1025
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,720
Every family has its own difficulties.

1026
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:48,120
You just asked me earlier,

1027
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,520
I'm a mother too, right?

1028
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:50,840
We both have children.

1029
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:53,000
But what I want to tell you is,

1030
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:55,000
we mothers

1031
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:57,480
should respect our kids' choices, right?
